#PLEASE README!! :)

# DOWNLOAD INSUTRCTIONS
To make this work end to end on your machine, clone the gitHub repo.
There are no extra downloads required beyond Python, pip, and the packages, as long as the CSV datasets are already included.

# BBB Permeability Model Workspace
The project currently includes three main scripts:
- `class_model_full_print_version.py`
  This file is my MAIN PROJECT SUBMISSION THAT YOU RUN. This uses the same baseline logic as the full-comment version, but keeps the print statements active throughout the script so you can see intermediate outputs as it runs. I used this version for refercing when creating the report.

- `class_model_full_comment_no_print_version.py`
  This is the reference version for the project logic, it is very informal. It keeps the full thought process and in-line comments from when I was developing, but most print statements are commented out.

- `class_model_new_seed.py`
  This is the stability-check version. It keeps the same modeling pipeline but uses a different random seed (`100` instead of the baseline `42`) to confirm the model behavior is reasonably stable. You can see the different outputs based on seed within the script_output_seed[seed#].txt files.

## Expected Workspace Layout
To reproduce my environment, keep this folder structure:

Project/
├── class_model_full_comment_no_print_version.py
├── class_model_full_print_version.py
├── class_model_new_seed.py
├── train/
│   └── desc_rdk_train.csv
└── external_test/
    └── desc_rdk_test.csv

The scripts expect:
- `train/desc_rdk_train.csv`
- `external_test/desc_rdk_test.csv`

If those files are missing, the scripts will fail when reading the datasets.

## Python Version
This workspace was built with:
- `Python 3.14.4`
- `pip 26.0.1`

## Running The Scripts
Run from the project root or else the paths wont resolve:

```bash
python class_model_full_comment_no_print_version.py
python class_model_full_print_version.py
python class_model_new_seed.py
```

## Important Runtime Note!!!!!! PLEASE READ !
These scripts generate Matplotlib plots during execution.
If you run them in a normal interactive Python session or terminal:
- the plot windows must be closed before the script continues to the next step
If you run in a non-interactive environment or with a backend like `Agg`, the scripts will close the plots automatically instead of waiting for you.
I will add them into the report, so no worries if they autoclose.

## Output Files
Depending on which script you run, the workspace may create:

- `script_output.txt`
- `model_comparison.csv`
- `desc_rdk_test_predictions.csv`

`class_model_full_print_version.py` and `class_model_new_seed.py` write printed output to `script_output.txt` in addition to showing it in the terminal for my testing purposes. You can see these files in the repo if you'd like to reference them.
